<br>
1: Mages aren't as dependant on gear as other classes. Very true, naked, and relying on ONLY what we can summon (and some malachite hehe) We are 90% as effective as with all gear. Very cool and go us. I think that was the MAIN point of the thread but it got broken down into these following statements.<br>
<br>
2: Flowing Thought items are NOT as important to us as they are to other classes. Nobody ever said they were not great to have, just it is not VITAL. Solo, mages can regen an incredible amount of mana with something as simple as eating pets, with a healer and mod rod it just gets insane. So, some mages like it when other classes get the FT items. Hurray for sharing. Great concept. As such, FT is STILL a great ability to have nobody argued that it was not, just we don't need it very much. Kinda like a necro, he doesn't need it THAT much either.<br>
<br>
3: Pet canna is the BEST way for a mage to regen mana with no healer. When it is said that Mod Rod is faster, yes, it is, but only if you have a healer or a SoA. Solo with nothing, eating pets is still the best way to get mana. And as for holding you malachite, jeebus, just get 2 10 slot bags and thats 400 pets. Get 4 bags if you want lol it's not that hard. <br>
<br>
I think the original post gets lost in the flames sometimes guys. Just stay on topic, and try to read a little into what other posters think and put yourself in their spot and try to see what point they are making. Here is the recap:<br>
<br>
1: Mages rely less on gear than other classes.<br>
2: FT is hella usefull, but not a class-definer, and not absolutely needed.<br>
3: Canna pets is #1 for solo mana regen for the average mage, Trods is #1 if you have a healer. <br>
<br>
Keep the info flowing gang I've become a way better mage since I learned about these boards.<br>
<br>
Baervon<br>
