claim Energy</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> returns mana based on one tenth the hitpoints, so I am surprised you made any profit at all.  It is well posted on this board, including this thread, that the best deal is either <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Greater Conjuration: Earth</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Monster Summoning 2</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, both of which cost 200 base mana to cast, 180 with specialization, etc., and return 260 mana upon reclaiming.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Jakin:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Which to me, your first point has been null and voided anyway. So we aren't made by our equipment, we are made by our AA and Summoning Efficiency 3 item??<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->You are also confusing two issues here.  In general, I do not find <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Flowing Thought</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> worth denying my guildmates because the mana generated is dwarfed by either serial pet reclamation or rods.  This is fully equipped.  But in the specific instance of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Nekkid ArchMage Soloing</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, the absence of any flowing thought or mind candy did not hamper me with excessive down time.  Naked except summonies, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> GC:E</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> costs me 150 mana to cast, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Reclaim Energy</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> costs about 5 mana, but returns 260 mana, so that is 105 net mana per reclaim.  Each cycle takes me 7 seconds to cast the pet and recover, reclaim takes another 4.5 seconds to cast and recover, or 11.5 seconds, call it two ticks.  105 mana in two ticks is about 50 mana per tick naked, not bad for a nekkid mage.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Jakin:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  And until you get elemental pact you just gotta carry a buttload of reagents?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Yeppers.  Just ask the other mages on this board, pre-59, pre-class AA, that <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>swear</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> by this technique.  Just because you haven't used it properly, or simply refuse to, does not mean it is not worthwhile.  A lot of mages are carrying pile of malachite anyway in order to chain pets.  And played properly and conservatively, little mana is used anyway, so it is not as if one has to chew through malachite between every fight.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Jakin:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  But I think the one thing i'm getting a kick out of, is thru all of this you are defending that you don't need FT items, when you still have not told me why the heck you don't want em.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Simple.  The mana generated by <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Flowing Thought</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is dwarfed by the mana generated by other means already available to me: pet reclamation, rods of transvergence, and horse.  Suppose my guild pulls <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Zelnithak</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Tome of Self Reflection</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> drops, with FT3.  How many casters in the guild want that tome?  Why, probably all of them that don't have the Tome?  Now, who are you going to award it to?  Probably a wizard, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Finteni</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Modred</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, to be honest.  Are you going to award it to Mister <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;Let me cover the ground with mod rods before rez effects have worn off&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> who obviously already has all the mana he needs and more?  I don't think so.  Hell, when there's a wipeout, I am rezzed after the clerics but before the bards, enchanters, and so on, because I can get the raid going again the fastest, and I don't need healing or mind candy to do it.  Whether rods or pets, I can give myself the equivalent of at least FT100 or much more with a healer, so FT3 is less than a 3% improvement.  On the other hand, it represents closer to a 10% improvement for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Finteni</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Modred</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  So guess what: I ain't even asking for it.  I am not so selfish as to take a miniscule increase in mana production and deny a guildmate for whom it matters much more.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Jakin:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  No equipment sets one arch mage above another.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->And <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>that</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> is my original point.  That even naked, we rock.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Baervon:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  I've really gotten TONS of info out of you guys.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Yeppers.  I learned about the joys of reclamation on this board, as well as chain casting pets.  From <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Rhion</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I learned that the last point of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Quick Summoning</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> was a good idea, and many other things.  From <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Jochan</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I have learned that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Improved Reclaim Energy</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> effects serial reclamation less than I had thought, and from <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Suzanna</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I learned that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Sirocco</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is still a damn fine spell, even with 200% specialization conjuration.  I come to these boards to learn, and to refine and share what I have learned.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Baevon:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  When it is said that Mod Rod is faster, yes, it is, but only if you have a healer or a SoA.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->  Check out <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showMessage?topicID=18.topic">Transvergence and The Complete Magician</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, where I summarize all that I have learned about rods.  For conjuration mages with rods, 3 HP ~= 1 Mana, so with natural regeneration, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Transon's Phantasmal Protection</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and the AA ability <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Improved Regeneration 3</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> (among the first AA most mages will get), that is already the equivalent of FT5.  No healer.  Rods are an important part of the mage's tool box, healing or no.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Baervon:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->   And as for holding you malachite, jeebus, just get 2 10 slot bags and thats 400 pets.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->For gems and such, I use a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Shaman Medicine Bag</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, made by combining a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Thick Grizzly Bear Skin</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> with a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Silk Cord</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, trivial at 60ish tailoring as I recall.  Although it will only hold small items, like gems, and does not reduce weight, it is cheaper than a tailor made pack, weighs less, and can be made more easily and cheaper.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Baervon:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Keep the info flowing gang I've become a way better mage since I learned about these boards.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Exactly.  And I've often learned the most from those I disagree with.<br>
