<br>
With mana regen via cana'ing pets&gt;KeI+FT15+TPP+MC3 (add med in and you &quot;might&quot; pass cana'ing alone, but cana'ing with those buffs would still negate any and all need to meditate)<br>
<br>
My thought on usefulness is:<br>
<br>
If I can go from 10ish m to fm in 2ish minutes (10-14 pets low spec, which will ONLY improve), could it be possible to consider FT useful? In the time I would have cana'ed to fm, I'd have gained 20 (ft1)-300 (ft15) mana from ft.  Even assuming FT15, when we are talking about gaining 2-3K mana in about 2 minutes, that 300 mana from the ft15 looks rather small, if your Raz and have the 5 second pets get some duct tape to keep your head from exploding when you watch your mana bar fill up.  If mana regen/tick cana'ing pets alone is 50 (to keep it simple), how useful is the mana regen from FT5?  Standing naked regen with no MC is 1, has anyone past lvl 10 ever considered that mana useful?  People laugh at others for getting MC2 and MC3 before other aa's would they do that if it was useful?  Why do we laugh at MC2 but treasure FT1?<br>
