<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Used GV: Water, 400 mana, 200 spec conjure, No Mana preservation<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You used the wrong pet.  Reclaim returns mana based on the hps of the pet at the time of the reclaim.  Water doesn't have a lot of hps as compared to some of the other pets.  Try it again with the 49 earth pet.  It takes half the mana to cast the pet and should return roughly the same mana back as the more expensive pet you used.<br>
<br>
I personally don't use Pet Canni very often while soloing.  I don't have to since I never truly &quot;solo&quot; since I have a second box druid.  But, in some cases it is still useful to pump mana up fast. <p><table border="0" width="100%">
